The paper discusses projection theorems of divergences, which are widely used in statistical inference and estimation. The paper also explores these projection theorems from the usual likelihood maximization approach and from the principle of sufficiency. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.ST (Statistics), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
